<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-12-14T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-12-14T03:00:00-05:00" n="605" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d605">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">493.11/871: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Schurman</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-12-14T16:00:00+08:00"><hi rend="italic">December 14,
                                        1922—4 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 5:04
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>494. On the resumption of Boxer indemnity payments this month I advise
                            retained portion be handled as it was before December 1917 when payments
                            were deferred. Same course might be followed with remitted portion also
                            but I consider present method of handling remitted portion preferable in
                            view of guarantees it affords. Please instruct by telegraph so I may
                            notify Foreign Office.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Schurman</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>